<p><h3>HAWUMPH</h3>
</p>
<p><img align="right" hspace="10" vspace="10" src="issue/23/images/hawumph1.gif">
<i>1) Your name is...</i>
<br>
<br>
The result of an unfortunate obsession with all thing draconian. I just love dragons, and wanted to see if I could beat this one. She's a right challenge. And I kept hearing the name so it seemed appropriate. Hawumph!
<br>
<br>
<i>2) Your favourite prefix is...</i>
<br>
<br>
Onomatopoeic. It does what it says on the tin!<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>3) Where are you now?</i>
<br>
<br>
In my office, in Hampton Hill, Middlesex, England, Europe. Replacing lots of modems that got fried in the storms last night (which won't be last night when this is printed but you did say now!)
<br>
<br>
<i>4) How did you make wiz?</i>
<br>
<br>
I assume you mean on MUDII, as opposed to MUD2.com. Basically I did seven tasks and got 204,800 points. But that's not what you want is it?
<br>
<br> 
OK. After a few mages I finally hung on to one, Wiley. I was on 203,633 points, and fighting rats. Someone powerful made a comment to which my reply was, "I am going for gold!"
<br>
<br> 
You see I had this obsession, not just to make wiz, but to do it by killing the dragon. Anyway I am about to set off to sea when I am attacked by something unknown. Ah, yes, a pk wizmort you are thinking. But no, it was a fearsome something, not someone.
<br>
<br>
To be precise, I had just been attacked by Matthew Kelly. <i>(Perhaps they meant Henry Kelly, he being the host of the show in question ;-) -ed)</i> I have to admit that an unknown quantity like a made-up mobile attacking you at that point of your career is ... unnerving?
<br>
<br> 
Enough to convince me that if I took my little buddy the hedgehog on a sightseeing tour, the rewards would be enough to make wiz, and now for some reason that was all that counted.I run around, and suddenly it whimpers, "Please drop me on fairy ring on island." With 20/20 hindsight, that of course wasn't right, it should have asked to be dropped IN the fairy ring on THE island. But I was nervous and didn't see it.
<br>
<br> 
Trouble is I needed 521 points and it was only worth 494. I could feel wizardly intervention piling up around me - I was cracking under the strain. So, quick calculation, run to summit of north mountain for a quick bonus, kill hedgehog, and - wizard!
<br>
<br>
<i>5) In real life, you are...</i>
<br>
<br>
Uh mental. Obviously! But I do PC support for a small number of companies. And have a games shop (PC games) which means I can play them all day and mud at night! Heaven.
<br>
<br>
<i>6) Tell us something we didn't know about you...</i>
<br>
<br>
The most fun I have had with something with an engine (I don't care if it's got 2 or 4 wheels, or just a propeller at the front, I like fast things) was doing aerobatics in a Tiger Moth.
<br>
<br> 
And I do mean doing, being in control, as opposed to just sitting there as a passenger!
</p>
<p align=center>
