<br>
<i>5) Tell us something we didn't know about you...</i>
<br>
<br>
I once made my own mini version of MUD to run on a Commodore C64. It was called "Leopards Dungeon" (named after one of my most well-known personas). The game was terrible but it kept me amused for months on end.
</p>
<p align=center>
-----------
</p>
<p><h3>LESTAT</h3>
</p>
<p><img align="right" hspace="10" vspace="10" src="issue/23/images/lestat1.gif">
<i>1) Your name is...</i>
<br>
<br>
Lestat - I've kinda regretted that since those damn movies came out. At the time I'd read the name in some obscure novel I'd picked up, and thought it had a nice ring to it. Ah well.
<br>
<br>
<i>2) Your favourite prefix is...</i>
<br>
<br>
Vampiric - kind of obligatory, really. 
<br>
<br>
<i>3) Where are you now?</i>
<br>
<br>
Hiding through the daylight hours...
<br>
<br>
<i>4) How did you make wiz?</i>
<br>
<br>
Ha. I had all sorts of grand schemes about this. I think I was just a bit crap at the game, as I'd been playing longer than lots of the wizzes I knew then. Took me ages to make wiz, but then I had some kind of pride thing that I had to make it as a pk. I was just a few k away and managed to persuade a mage to come out and fight me for my last reset - summoned him to a locked room in the monastery, but bollixed it up on the reattacks: "k kk wi ax....." forgetting that I had a staff, not a pick. Ah well. 
<br>
<br>
Then the plan changed to this scheme I'd been toying with for ages. The idea was to get to within a couple of points of going over, by carefully calculating the amount of treasure to swamp, then attacking the dragon and while in the fight, eating a flower.... Of course, I messed it up by forgetting that the second icon I swamped would be worth more, 'cos the treasure value would go up. Still - it'd be a grand way to make it if anyone else can manage it, I think.
<br>
<br>
<i>5) In real life, you are...</i>
<br>
<br>
Not a cold blooded killer, honest. 
<br>
<br>
<i>6) Tell us something we didn't know about you...</i>
<br>
<br>
See (5).
</p>
